.\" Manpage for rlibstr (part of reddlibc).
.\" Contact redd@redds.be to correct errors or typos.
.TH man 3 "11 November 2023" "1.0" "rlibstr man page (reddlibc)"
.SH NAME
rlibstr, cleanstr, lowerstr, upperstr
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include <rlibstr.h>

.B char *cleanstr(char *strToClean);

.B char *lowerstr(char *str);

.B char *upperstr(char *str);
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B cleanstr()
.R function cleans a string by removing \(rsr and \(rsn at the end of the string. It returns a (char *), it takes:

.B \t strToClean:
.R The string that will be cleaned.

The
.B lowerstr()
.R function converts upper-case string to lower-case string. It returns a (char *), it takes:

.B \t str:
.R The string that will be converted.

The
.B upperstr()
.R function converts lower-case string to upper-case string. It returns a (char *), it takes:

.B \t str:
.R The string that will be converted.
.SH NOTES
When including this header, make sure to link reddlibc.a (in /usr/lib/ on default reddlibc installs) when compiling.
.SH SEE ALSO
rlibinput(3), rlibchar(3), rlibstdio(3), rlibint(3)
.SH BUGS
No known bugs. Although some consider that they are a feature in C.
